                                    <h3>Comments by John Strong</h3>
                                    <p></p>
                                    <p>
                                    I personally visited the home of this woman. She is very
                                    severely handicapped and desperately poor, but she has
                                    adapted to her circumstances with truly remarkable 
                                    ingenuity. The whole chicken coop idea with the door next
                                    to the floor so that she could attend to their needs from
                                    the floor was a stroke of genius.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                    Nevertheless, even though she has adapted to her circumstances
                                    remarkably well, she would benefit enormously from receiving
                                    financial support.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                    The World Vision staff has not had much direct contact with this
                                    woman, but one of their sector leaders, Antonio has. When
                                    Antonio learned that we were looking for the poorest of the poor
                                    in his area, he led us to this woman's hut.
